# This file describes the installation of SpeciesGeoCoder on Mac OSX, 
# GNU/Linux and Windows system.

===========================================
# Content of this file
1.) For the impatient
2.) Dependencies
3.) Installing on Mac OSX.
4.) Installing on Windows using Cygwin
5.) Installing on GNU/Linux
6.) Installing the development version
7.) Example data
===========================================

=====================
1.) For the impatient
=====================
wget https://github.com/mtop/speciesgeocoder/archive/master.zip
unzip master.zip
cd speciesgeocoder-master/
make
sudo make install


=================
2.) Dependencies*
=================
argparse (Module included in python v2.7) 
make
gcc
R (only needed if you want to use the plot functions)

*The programs 'make' and 'gcc' are only needed if the pre-compiled 
versions of gdalinfo and gdallocationinfo does now work on your system. 
Both 'make' and 'gcc' should be installed on a regular GNU/Linux 
system. Mac OSX and Windows/Cygwin users can find installation 
instructions below.


==========================
3.) Installing on Mac OSX.
==========================
'make' and 'gcc' are part of the package 'Xcode' that is available on 
Appstore. After installation, open Xcode and go to: 
Preferences -> Downloads -> Components -> Command Line Tools, and 
install the commandline tools of Xcode. Then follow these steps:

a. Direct your browser to the following URL (a compressed file will 
	thenbe automatically downloaded):

	https://github.com/mtop/speciesgeocoder/archive/master.zip

b. Unzip the file by clicking on it.
c. Open a terminal window and use the command "cd" and move into the 
	directory "speciesgeocoder-master/"
d. Type 'make' to compile GDAL binaries.
e. Copy and paste the following command into your terminal window
	to make sure everything works as expected:

	./geocoder.py -l example_data/localities.csv -p example_data/polygons.txt -t example_data/*.tif

f.	Then run the command 'sudo make install' to install the package 
	in /usr/local/bin


======================================
4.) Installing on Windows using Cygwin
======================================
Follow the instructions in the file doc/HOWTO_Cygwin_installation.txt
to install Cygwin and all dependencies to SpeciesGeoCoder.

# Copy and paste the following commands in a Cygwin terminal window
wget https://github.com/mtop/speciesgeocoder/archive/master.zip
unzip master.zip
cd speciesgeocoder-master/
make 
make install 

===========================
5.) Installing on GNU/Linux
===========================
wget https://github.com/mtop/speciesgeocoder/archive/master.zip
unzip master.zip
cd speciesgeocoder-master/
make
sudo make install


======================================
6.) Installing the development version
======================================
git clone git@github.com:mtop/speciesgeocoder.git
cd speciesgeocoder/
make distclean
make


================
7.) Example data
================
Examples of the the type of input files used by 'speciesgeocoder' 
is located in the directory example_data/. You can test the program 
by typing the following command in the 'speciesgeocoder' directory.

./geocoder.py -l example_data/localities.csv -p example_data/polygons.txt -t example_data/*.tif

